    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "It is arguable though that the library then becomes the extension itself. This is similar to what we were talking about yesterday with @soltanmm with the Python extension. The goal is that people should be able to do a gem install or a pip install on the directory, and let the setup do its work. If it deems necessary to embed the full grpc library in it, then so be it. A one-liner to install the extension, without additional hassle.\n\nAs far as portability is concerned, mkmf creates a makefile itself, meaning that having \"make\" is a non-negotiable requirement from any extconf.rb around. Meaning that invoking make should always work.\n"
  },
